<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880406-0017 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: Allied-Signal Inc. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> UK ALD </CO><IN> CHM </IN><TEXT>   Allied-Signal Inc. and Union Carbide Corp. said they plan to form a venture to supply technology, products, engineered systems and services to petroleum, petrochemical and natural gas industries world-wide. Terms weren't disclosed.    The new business, which will be called UOP, combines Union Carbide's Catalysts, Absorbents andamp; Process Systems business with Allied-Signal's UOP Inc. unit, which provides process technology.    The units of Danbury, Conn.-based Union Carbide and Morristown, N.J.-based Allied-Signal have combined annual sales of about $600 million. The companies said completion of the transaction is expected by midyear. </TEXT></DOC>